Parliament, Tuesday, 25 September 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Police will tomorrow (26 September 2018) be briefed by the South African Police Service on matters related to roles and responsibilities and safety of the national legislature. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 26 September 2018
	Venue: Committee Room V475, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building
	Time: 10:00 ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE ACTING CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON POLICE, MR FRANCOIS BEUKMAN For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact committee’s media officer: Name: Mr Justice Molafo
	Tel: 021 403 8444
	Cell: 081 424 7481
	Email: jmolafo@parliament.gov.za Anybody over the age of 18 can participate indirectly in Parliament simply by voting in the elections.Read more